SECTION B â€” Core Houserules (Defaults)

ğŸ• Action Economy Exchange
Rule: A character may use an Action to perform any Bonus Action,
as long as they do not repeat something already used as a Bonus Action this round.
Rationale: Expands tactical flexibility without breaking economy balance.

ğŸ§´ Healing Potion Variance Healing
Rule:
- Consuming a healing potion as a Bonus Action â†’ roll normally for HP recovered.
- Consuming as an Action â†’ automatically heal the potionâ€™s maximum HP value.
Rationale: Encourages tactical choice between time and reliability.
Integration: Hooks into RNG Policy (roll vs. max mode).

âš”ï¸ Perkins Critical
Rule:
- When you score a Critical Hit, your bonus dice deal maximum damage instead of rolling.
- Example: â€œOne die max crit.â€ (1d8 weapon = 8 + modifiers).
Rationale: Streamlines crit math and makes hits more cinematic.

